<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: GMS just make things worse. Got suspended for no reason.</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Fenick">Fenick</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 12:45 p.m. 26/7/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: GMS just make things worse. Got suspended for no reason.<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/tunare.cgi?read=123" TARGET=_self>Re: GMS just make things worse. Got suspended for no reason.</A> (Selki)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>Just a couple of comments on your points.

<P>In reference to the second point, since you are paying to join an "online gaming club" you allow yourself to become a subject of the rules and charters of that club. The constitutional laws that govern us as US citizens are not capable of forcing an organization to abide by those laws. You subject yourself to their contract when you agree to pay them to play.
<P>As far as point 3 is concerned, be careful when using here-say to make your point. It is easy to exaggerate when you are upset and trying to make a point. Use outside sources, impartial witnesses and source testimony. If you don't have that, YOU can not say that the GM's were ignoring someone.
<P>You seem quite surprised in point 4 that you purchased software that contained some bugs and incomplete programming. First, you should have been aware that the game is constantly being updated therefore incomplete. Every new aspect goes through rigorous testing on the test server prior to release however it is a program designed by humans and therefore imperfect. Bugs happen. It is because of the efforts of the tech department fixing those bugs that you have a game to complain about at all.
<P>There will always be something to complain about, especially when things aren't going your way. So please becareful when accusing to think things through and not jump to premature conclusions.
<P>Fenick
<BR>Ranger of Innorruk
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
